Map conventional aliases — formal long-form names ("Republic of X", "Federal Republic of X", "Kingdom of X", "Commonwealth of X"), native-language forms (Brasil ↔ Brazil, Deutschland ↔ Germany, México ↔ Mexico, 日本 ↔ Japan, 中国 ↔ China), abbreviations (UK / USA / KSA / ROK / PRC / RSA), and short / colloquial forms (Britain, Korea, Türkiye ↔ Turkey) — to the canonical name for that member state. The European Union and the African Union, while G20 members, are not sovereign member-states and fall outside the country axis for this task.
